column3: Definition
Term related to Service Delivery
Term that indicates the delivery of associated service is required and obligated
Term related to Analytics
Term that indicates analytics by 2nd and 3rd parties is allowed
Term that indicates analytics by 2nd and 3rd parties is disallowed
Term that indicates analytics by 2nd Party is allowed
Term that indicates analytics by 3rd Party is disallowed
Term related to Tracking
Term that indicates Tracking by 2nd and 3rd parties is allowed
Term that indicates Tracking 2nd Party is allowed
Term that indicates Tracking by 2nd and 3rd parties is disallowed
Term that indicates Tracking 3rd Party is disallowed
Term that indicates Tracking is allowed but only if it does not use any PII
Term that indicates Tracking is allowed but only if it does not involve Fingerprinting
Term that indicates Tracking involving use of PII is not allowed
Term that indicates Tracking involving use of Fingerprinting is not allowed
Term related to Profiling
Term that indicates Profiling is allowed
Term that indicates Profiling is allowed but only by the 1st Party
Term that indicates Profiling is not allowed
Term that indicates Profiling is not allowed by 3rd Parties
Term that indicates Profiling is allowed but only if it uses non-PII
Term that indicates Profiling is allowed but only if it does not involve Fingerprinting
Term that indicates Profiling involving use of PII is not allowed
Term that indicates Profiling involving use of Fingerprinting is not allowed
Term related to Data Sharing
Term that indicates Data Sharing is allowed
Term that indicates Data Sharing is not allowed
Term that indicates Data Sharing for fully anonymised data is not allowed
Term that indicates data sharing with third party is allowed
Term that indicates data sharing with third party is disallowed

column2: Sharing Anonymised Data with 3rd Party Allowed
column3: Term that indicates data sharing only of anonymised data with third party is allowed

column2: Sharing Anonymised Data with 3rd Party Disallowed
column3: Term that indicates data sharing of full anonymised data with third party is disallowed

column2: Sharing Non-Anonymised Data with 3rd Party Disallowed
column3: Term that indicates data sharing of non-anonymised data with third party is disallowed
Term related to interpretation of the Term(s) using deontic logic
Term that indicates a permissive interpretation where if something is not prohibited or if there are no rules governing it, then it is assumed to be permitted
Term that indicates a prohibitive interpretation where if something is not permitted or if there are no rules governing it, then it is assumed to be prohibited
Term related to resolving conflicts in Term(s)
Term that indicates a conflict should be resolved by preferring the permission over the prohibition i.e. if something is both prohibited and permitted, it is assumed to be permitted
Term that indicates a conflict should be resolved by preferring the prohibition over the permission i.e. if something is both prohibited and permitted, it is assumed to be prohibited
Term that indicates a conflict should be resolved by discarding the conflicting terms i.e. removing all terms that are in conflict
Term that indicates a conflict should be resolved using the specified method but only for this context i.e. other contexts that have their own conflict resolution method should not be overridden
Term that indicates this conflict method should be used to resolve all conflicts across contexts i.e. other contexts that have their own conflict resolution method should be overridden
Term that indicates the behaviour of the Agent
Term that indicates the behaviour of the Agent in relation to requests
Term that indicates the Agent should allow requests to be made

column2: Agent Allows Requests Only Known Party
column3: Term that indicates the Agent should allow requests to be made but only from prior known parties

column2: Agent Allows Requests Only Prior Agreement Party
column3: Term that indicates the Agent should allow requests to be made but only from prior known parties with whom an agreement was established in the past
Term that indicates the Agent should not allow any requests to be made
Term that indicates the behaviour of the Agent in relation to negotiations
Term that indicates the Agent should allow negotiations

column2: Agent Allows Negotiation Only Known Party
column3: Term that indicates the Agent should allow negotiations but only from known parties

column2: Agent Allows Negotiation Only Prior Agreement Party
column3: Term that indicates the Agent should allow negotiations but only from known parties with whom an agreement was established in the past
Term that indicates the Agent should not allow any negotiations
Term that indicates the applicability of Privacy Preference(s)
Term that indicates the privacy preference always applies in all contexts and should always be used in agreements and negotiations
Term that indicates the privacy preference never applies in any context and should never be used in agreements or negotiations
Term that indicates the privacy preference conditionally applies i.e. it should only be used in agreements and negotiations if the associated condition is satisfied within the context
Term that indicates portability of data from service provider to individual
column7: Data portability means that you are entitled to ask organisations that hold records about you (your personal data) to be sent in a modern, useful format either to you directly, or to another organisation/ app that you nominate. Examples of that might be your bank transactions (via Open Banking or similar), your home energy use, your vehicle use and many more.

Term that indicates data should be ported or made available on request
Term that indicates data should be ported or made available to third party
Term that indicates data portability is not required to be provided

Term that indicates transparency regarding purposes involved for processing of data and technologies is not required to be provided
Term that indicates transparency regarding identities and involvement of parties in specific roles as an obligation
Term that indicates transparency regarding identities and involvement of parties in specific roles is obligated

Term that indicates transparency regarding identities and involvement of parties in specific roles is obligated upon request
Term that indicates transparency regarding identities and involvement of parties in specific roles is not required to be provided
